# Python Backend Standards

## API Contract
- Each API method should validate required params first and return clear `public.returnMsg(False, "...")` on failure.
- Success/failure responses should keep stable shapes to avoid front-end parsing issues.

## SQL and Shell Safety
- Never build SQL with untrusted raw strings when avoidable.
- If shell execution is required, validate and sanitize inputs before assembling commands.
- Avoid global MySQL replication operations without channel targeting.

## Error Handling
- Use explicit `try/except` around I/O, SQL, and remote calls.
- Return actionable error messages with context, but never include plaintext passwords/tokens.

## Logging
- Use structured and concise logs per source/channel.
- Include `source_id` and `channel_name` in operational logs when available.
